text: I make the decision to head back to hospital where I'm hospitalized for 3 days for severe asthma attack. I get discharged with more prescriptions and head home to rest for the day.

author: hesshonza
text: I take two inhales of my inhaler and it doesnt work. I end up take 4 more puffs and I'm still coughing desperately, I cant breathe. I grab my phone and turn on the flashlight and put my shoes on and grab my backpack. I pass thru the living room and my mom's k.o'd..

author: hesshonza
text:
I finally lay in bed and start to doze off and fall asleep.
Tell me how I woke the fuck up at 4AM EXACTLY from a coughing fit where I cant fuck breathe and while I'm coughing my air purifier just shuts off. By itself. I start to freak out because I'm starting to feel paranoid..

author: hesshonza
text: I take it as a sign from my spirit guide that I'm getting really paranoid and I should lay off the readings for a while. I put away my cards and put em under my pillow, and turn off the lights. My air purifier is on automatic & still on, so I get into bed, sitting upright..

author: hesshonza
text: My cold gets so bad that it triggers my seasonal asthma and I check into the hospital with my mom. They give me some aerosol treatment and send me home with inhaler prescriptions that I get filled @ the pharmacy near our new apt. We make it home and we get ready for bed.

author: hesshonza
text: Fast forward up until Dec. 15, the day we moved into our new apt. I had a really bad cold, everything was cluttered in the house and the a/c didnt work, outlets didnt work - it was just a hectic, emotional/physical mess.

author: hesshonza
text: So I used it. And I loved what it was telling me. I read a but more and agreed with the concept of a "gentle, caring spirit guide" that was watching over me, trying to give me advice on how to better my life, calm my anxieties and basically say everything was gonna be ok.

author: hesshonza
text: Tarot cards lead me to crystals and then that lead me straight to wiccan magic spell stuff and this wasnt the first time I hadn't played around with the stuff. But I decided to really get into this. I ordered a rider waite tarot deck, it's apparently a classic.

author: hesshonza
text: I, on the other hand, was a bit of an agnostic. So, I dabbled in researching other types of religions and just curiously learning. While in my living situation, idk how, I ended up reading up on tarot cards and got hooked on the concept.

author: hesshonza
text: That was Nov.16. We were both staying at other people's places. My mom @ my grandma's & I was at my bf's. While everything was going on I was having a hard time coping with the sudden adjustment. My mom is a hardcore Pentecostal Christian woman so, religion was always in my life.
